{
  "name": "Medical Release Venom Shower",
  "type": "spell",
  "img": "systems/n5eb/assets/Icons%20%26%20Images/Icons/Medical.png",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You begin to generate poisonous medical chakra and release it, creating a rain of poisonous needles.</p><p>Select a space in the air that you can see. You create a poisonous gas cloud that begins to rain down poisonous needles filling a 20-foot radius, 50-foot-high cylinder. Each creature in the cylinder must make a Dexterity saving throw. A creature takes 6d6 poison damage on a failed save and half as much on a successful save.</p><p>The ground this area affects generates poisonous thorns on the ground that lasts for 1 minute. Creatures who that enter the area of poisonous thorns takes 4d4 poison damage for each 5 feet they move through the affected area. Once a space has been moved through, the thorns break becoming inert.</p><p>At Higher Ranks: For each rank you cast this jutsu above B-Rank, increase the cost of this jutsu by 3 and the damage by 1d6.</p>",
